headline.main: TOBRUK SIEGE COST AUSTRALIA 500 MEN; Units Dashing to Meet British Pass Graves of Comrades -- Emerge Without Loss

lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia, Nov. 24 (Australian Associated Press) -- The Australians who broke out of Tobruk to join the advancing imperial forces in Libya suffered no loss of life in the engagement, but left behind in a cemetery the graves of more than 500 Australians who lost their lives during the long siege, according to word received from Cairo today by Army Minister Francis M. Forde.
abstract: Tobruk siege cost Australians 500 men; disclosed that bulk of Australians were replaced by Brit, Poles and Indians
